import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['budgetYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['budgetYear'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    data = data.groupby('budgetYear').mean().reset_index()
    
    plt.plot(data['budgetYear'], data['value'])
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.title("What is the trend of budget forecasts over the years?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['value'], bins=20)
    plt.xlabel('Forecasted Budget Value as a Percentage of GDP')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    ax = plt.gca()
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of budget forecast values?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['forecastYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['forecastYear'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    avg_values = data.groupby('forecastYear')['value'].mean()
    
    ax = avg_values.plot(kind='bar')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the average budget forecast value for each forecastYear?", wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
